            <abstract>
                <p> The text, attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop23"/>, is the collection of the statutes of the Coptic Church
                    approved on <date>2 June 1985</date> (the feast of <persName ref="PRS4306GabraMa"/>). 
                    The statutes were issued in Arabic and English; the translator, ʾabuna Maqaryos, used for his translation the Arabic version.
                    The text contains 89 chapters or statutes (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ዓንቀጽ</foreign>). The last one concerns the order of 
                    making changes in the statutes 
                    (the procedure in stages, marked <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሀ</foreign>, 
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሓ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መ</foreign>).  </p>
